The paper deals with the computation of graph spanners, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves probabilistic analysis and combinatorics, which are relevant to the sub-categories of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and network economics (cs.NE). Finally, the paper introduces a new concept of local computation algorithms for spanners, which can be considered as a sub-topic of distributed computing (cs.DC).
